-- AFRICA WEEK AHEAD: Ugandan Rate Decision, Kenyan Inflation Data
-- B y   P a u l   R i c h a r d s o n
-- 2012-02-27T02:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-27/africa-week-ahead-ugandan-rate-decision-kenyan-inflation-data.html
Uganda ’s central bank will announce
its next interest-rate decision on March 1 when it publishes its
monetary policy statement. The bank cut its benchmark lending
rate by one percentage point to 22 percent on Feb. 1.  Kenya’s statistics agency is scheduled to release February
consumer-inflation data on Feb. 29, a spokesman for the agency
said today. Inflation slowed to 18.3 percent in January from
18.9 percent a month earlier, the agency said on Jan. 31. 